body:
Last Window: The Secret of Cape West - Review. A fantastic adventure game that still holds up well

Throughout its entire lifespan, the DS had been a popular medium for Graphic Adventure games, from hits such as the Ace Attorney franchise to lesser known titles like Time Hollow. Back in 2007, we saw one such example in the form of Hotel Dusk: Room 215. Developed by Cing, also known for the Trace Memory/Another Code series, and published by Nintendo, it was a hit amongst Nintendo fans. So it was…

summary: Recently I bought Little Dragons Cafe! The game follows two siblings whose mother gets sick because of the mix of dragon blood...
body:
Recently I bought Little Dragons Cafe! The game follows two siblings whose mother gets sick because of the mix of dragon blood within her.

Along comes a wizard who tells you to help her you must raise a dragon by feeding it lots of food and making it grow!

With your mum sick you have to also look after the cafe, many quirky visitors come along and you have to help them with their stories!

You must find fragments of recipes and increase the cafe’s reputation.

This game is great I adore it, it’s by the same people who make Story Of Seasons.
